." Manpage for rmeta
.TH RMETA 1 "July 2026" "rMetaCLI v0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rmeta \- local file metadata scrubber
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rmeta [options] FILES...
.SH DESCRIPTION
rMeta is a local-only file metadata scrubber for privacy-focused users. It removes metadata from files without sending data anywhere.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B cleanup
Remove all session files and directories.
.TP
.B download OUTPUT_DIR
Download processed files to the specified output directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --gpg-key <path>
Use GPG public key for encryption.
.TP
.B --sha256
Generate SHA256 hashfiles for processed files.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Show actions without modifying files.
.TP
.B --verbose, -v
Enable detailed logging.
.TP
.B --clean-after
Automatically clean session files after processing.
.TP
.B --filetype <type>
Only process files of a certain type (e.g., pdf, docx).
.TP
.B --r
Recursively process files from directories.
.TP
.B --config <path>
Use a custom config file.
.TP
.B --version
Print version info.
.TP
.B --help
Print help for commands.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B UPLOAD_FOLDER
Set the session directory (default: /tmp/rmeta_uploads).
.TP
.B SESSION_TIMEOUT
Session cleanup interval in seconds (default: 600).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B rmeta --r --filetype pdf /docs
.TP
.B rmeta --gpg-key mykey.pub --sha256 --clean-after file1.pdf file2.docx
.TP
.B rmeta --dry-run --verbose file1.pdf file2.docx
.TP
.B rmeta --cleanup
.SH AUTHOR
KitQuietDev
.SH SEE ALSO
rmeta(1), pyinstaller(1)
